					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/steeltitan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1871133); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1871133&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204703" alt="Steeltitan" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1871133)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/steeltitan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1871133); return false;" >Steeltitan</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456855429 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Mar 2016 18:03</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2465885">
									

<p>How are there a hundred ways to interpret that? It seemed fairly obvious. The man was a Church of the Broken God spy. He has been mostly replaced by mechanics on the inside, and finally decides to leave his human body behind, but keeps it intact so it can run errands for him.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>As it moves, I can hear the the tiny little servos implanted throughout it, located at key joints and around the vital organs.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>You can only get so much out of an artificial neural unit; fusing it to the spine didn't leave a lot of room to work with.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>These show the body is mechanically supported. It's not just the skin, but most of the muscles and organs, which are not needed by his now mechanical body.</p>
<p>As for the girl praying, she's a member of a foundation task force sent to Venus with the rest of the colonists. She's praying because she's stressed and trying to get ready before landing. We can also see other task force members trying to relieve stress through various methods.</p>
<p>Overall, the message seemed pretty clear to me. Can't figure out where you got &quot;bouncy blue ball&quot; from, can't find it in the stories.</p>
<p>I do have once suggestion though. The article might be more clear if you had a link to the original SCP these people are sent to explore somewhere on the page, or the specific MTF series these articles belong to.</p>

							</div>

								
					
