<blockquote>
<p>Please do not flame me for my opinions :(</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Crayne addressed your comments. There's no flaming going on.</p>
<p>Allow me to further address your comments.</p>
<p>You display no evidence in your commentary that you've done anything more than skim the piece over, let alone thought about it for any length of time. You can't even be bothered to leave feedback with proper spelling or grammar. And then you say stuff like &quot;feels like its just written so you can get words down,&quot; while having the temerity to act butthurt when Crayne offers a counterpoint.</p>
<p>I've been downvoted and criticized dozens of times on this site. It's never bothered me, because in those cases people have taken the time to read something that I've written, and offered me the benefit of their insight, which has helped me to improve as a writer. I welcome that kind of scrutiny.</p>
<p>You, on the other hand, don't even appear to have a proper grasp of basic English. Feel free to vote however you wish on my work or anything else on the site. But I sure as hell am not going to take any commentary from you seriously. I have no respect for amateurish, ill-informed criticism, wherever it appears. And that's the last I'm going to say on the matter.</p>

							</div>

								
